# Note: This env var was previously used for client-side Big Data Cloud reverse geocoding
# (see commented lines in the README.md file). Now secured via Netlify serverless functions (/api/reverse-geocode).
# For local dev testing of original client-side (insecure) setup, add your key here.
# Restart `npm run dev` after adding to .env.
# Copy to .env or .env.local (gitignored) for local use.
VITE_BDC_API_KEY=your_bigdatacloud_api_key_here

# To use netlify serverless function add API key here but without the "VITE_" prefix
# Go to netlify.com and open your site
# Click Site configuration in the left sidebar
# Click Environment variables
# Click Add a variable → Add a single variable
# Set:
# Key Field -> type in "BDC_API_KEY"
# Values Field -> type in/copy and paste your actual Big Data Cloud key
# Click Save
BDC_API_KEY=your_bigdatacloud_api_key_here
